        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 3:48PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sweet Water, or 13 miles southwest of Linden, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Demopolis, Linden, Uniontown, Jefferson, Thomaston, Sweet Water,
Myrtlewood, Faunsdale, Dayton, Nanafalia, Consul, Surginer, Putnam,
Freddie Jones Field, Shawnee, Pin Hook, Magnolia, Wayne, Miller, and
Chickasaw State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
